NB. Find the greatest common divisor (GCD) of two non-negative integers.
NB.
NB. gcd(a, b) = a b = 0
NB.             b a = 0
NB.             gcd(a mod b, b) a >= b
NB.             gcd(a, b mod a) a < b
NB.
NB. Input
NB. Two integers a and b (0≤a,b≤2⋅10^9).
NB.
NB. Output
NB. Print the greatest common divisor of a and b.
NB.
NB. Examples
NB. Input #1
NB. 42 24
NB.
NB. Answer #1
NB. 6

1!:2&2 (42 +. 24)
1!:2&2 (48 +. 2)
1!:2&2 (17 +. 13)

